"{\n    \"Title\": \"Year ended March 31, 20201. Significant accounting policies (continued):\",\n    \"row 1\": \"(d) Non-financial assets:\",\n    \"row 2\": \"Non-financial assets are not available to discharge existing liabilities and are held for use\",\n    \"row 3\": \"in the provision of services. They have useful lives extending beyond the current year\",\n    \"row 4\": \"and are not intended for sale in the ordinary course of operations.\",\n    \"row 5\": \"(i) Tangible capital assets:\",\n    \"row 6\": \"Tangible capital assets are recorded at cost which includes amounts that are directly\",\n    \"row 7\": \"attributable to acquisition, construction, development or betterment of the asset. The\",\n    \"row 8\": \"cost, less residual value of the tangible capital assets, excluding land is amortized on\",\n    \"row 9\": \"a straight-line basis over the estimated useful lives of the assets as follows:\",\n    \"row 10\": \"Estimated Life\",\n    \"row 11\": \"Asset - Years\",\n    \"row 12\": \"Computer equipment 4 years\",\n    \"row 13\": \"Vehicles 15 years\",\n    \"row 14\": \"Furniture and equipment 5 - 10 years\",\n    \"row 15\": \"Machinery and equipment 6 - 25 years\",\n    \"row 16\": \"Water systems 10 - 50 years\",\n    \"row 17\": \"Roads 25 - 50 years\",\n    \"row 18\": \"Housing 25 - 40 years\",\n    \"row 19\": \"Buildings 25 - 40 years\",\n    \"row 20\": \"Annual amortization is charged in the year of acquisition and in the year of disposal.\",\n    \"row 21\": \"Assets under construction are not amortized until the asset is available for productive\",\n    \"row 22\": \"use.\",\n    \"row 23\": \"(ii) Natural resources:\",\n    \"row 24\": \"Natural resources that have not been purchased are not recognized as assets in the\",\n    \"row 25\": \"financial statements.\",\n    \"row 26\": \"(iii) Works of art and cultural and historic assets:\",\n    \"row 27\": \"Works of art and cultural and historic assets are not recorded as assets in these\",\n    \"row 28\": \"consolidated financial statements.\"\n}"